prompt:
Describe a scenario where using data analysis can lead to unexpected discoveries or insights.
As a financial planner, I once analyzed data related to my clients' spending habits during holidays. I discovered that one client had consistently spent much more than their average monthly budget on Thanksgiving day for several years in a row. Upon further investigation, it turned out that this individual was supporting their extended family financially due to difficult circumstances they were facing privately. With this newfound insight, I was able to help them create a sustainable financial plan that accounted for these unexpected expenses and provided long-term financial security.
